<h4>2.2.1 Adding Instructors</h4>
<p>When the admin clicks the <b>Instructors</b> button under the <b>Databases</b> menu, the scheduler program displays the following page.</p>
<div>
    <a href="images/desk_manage_instructors_empty.png"><img src="images/desk_manage_instructors_empty.png" width="500px" /></a>
    <p class="caption">Figure 2.2.1-1 shows the instructor database management screen.</p>
</div>
<p>At first, the database is empty. To add an instructor, an administrator clicks the <b>Add</b> button. The scheduler program shows the following dialog to add a new instructor to the database.</p>
<div>
   <a href="images/desk_manage_instructors_add.png"><img src="images/desk_manage_instructors_add.png" width="500px" /></a>
   <p class="caption">Figure 2.2.1-2a shows the add instructor dialog.</p>
</div>
<div>
   <a href="images/desk_manage_instructors_add_filled.png"><img src="images/desk_manage_instructors_add_filled.png" width="500px" /></a>
   <p class="caption">Figure 2.2.1-2b shows the add instructor dialog.</p>
</div>
<p>After clicking the <b>Submit</b> button on the dialog, the table is filled out based on the information in the Cal Poly database. The administrator repeats the process for all of the other instructors that he or she wishes to add.</p>
<div>
   <a href="images/desk_manage_instructors_afteradd.png"><img src="images/desk_manage_instructors_afteradd.png" width="500px" /></a>
   <p class="caption">Figure 2.2.1-3 shows how the instructor table will look after adding one instructor</p>
</div>
<p>After repeating the process for one more instructor, the table looks like the following.</p>
<div>
   <a href="images/desk_manage_instructors_afteradd2.png"><img src="images/desk_manage_instructors_afteradd2.png" width="500px" /></a>
   <p class="caption">Figure 2.2.1-4 shows how the instructor table will look after adding one more instructor</p>
</div>
<p>The table sorts the instructors by their Cal Poly user names, and after adding many more instructors, the table will look like this.</p>
<div>
   <a href="images/desk_manage_instructors.png"><img src="images/desk_manage_instructors.png" width="500px" /></a>
   <p class="caption">Figure 2.2.1-5: This image depicts the instructor management screen after adding instructors.</p>
</div>
<p>If an administrator wishes to edit an existing instructor, one clicks the instructor's entry in the table and then clicks the <b>Edit</b> button, displaying the following dialog.</p>
<div>
   <a href="images/desk_manage_instructors_edit.png"><img src="images/desk_manage_instructors_edit.png" width="500px" /></a>
   <p class="caption">Figure 2.2.1-6 shows the edit instructor dialog.</p>
</div>
<p>The administrator makes the necessary edits, and after clicking the <b>Submit</b> button, the edits are saved to the database and the table is updated.</p>
<p>To remove an instructor from the database, the administrator clicks <b>Delete</b> after highlighting an instructor's entry by clicking it.</p>
<div>
   <a href="images/desk_manage_instructors_delete_before.png"><img src="images/desk_manage_instructors_delete_before.png" width="500px" /></a>
   <p class="caption">Figure 2.2.1-7: Selecting the instructor to delete</p>
</div>
<p>For example, if an administrator wants to remove Alex Dekhtyar from the instructor database, first, he or she would need to click Alex Dekhtyar's record in the database.</p>
<div>
   <a href="images/desk_manage_instructors_delete_after.png"><img src="images/desk_manage_instructors_delete_after.png" width="500px" /></a>
   <p class="caption">Figure 2.2.1-8: After deleting an instructor</p>
</div>
<p>The instructor is permanently removed from the instructor database, removing their preferences and other associated information from the database.</p>
